OL,3,CHigh school students learn about death
OL,4,Cand grieving as part of special course
OL,6,FHigh school students have been
OL,7,Flearning about a difficult topic which
OL,8,Faffects us all, as they take lessons
OL,9,Fin death and bereavement.
OL,11,FThe pupils at Castle Douglas High
OL,12,FSchool are engaging in a three-day
OL,13,Fcourse called 'The D Word', which aims
OL,14,Fto help pupils explore their feelings
OL,15,Faround bereavement, and suggests
OL,16,Fcoping mechanisms.
OL,18,FThe course was designed by a
OL,19,Fcelebrant, who says she wants to take
OL,20,Faway "the fear of the unknown".
