OL,3,CHigh school students learn about death
OL,4,Cand grieving as part of special course
OL,6,FAileen Palmer told ITV Border: "We
OL,7,Fstarted to look at the barriers to
OL,8,Ftalking about death in society, and
OL,9,Fhow it's increasingly hidden from our
OL,10,Fculture.
OL,12,F"We then looked at what happens in a
OL,13,Fnormal death, and what needs to happen
OL,14,Fpractically: power of attorney and
OL,15,Fwills."
OL,17,FOne pupil, Kirstie Benson, said the
OL,18,Fcourse had been helpful, as she deals
OL,19,Fwith losing her mother when she was in
OL,20,Fprimary school.
